Plugins must:

Use only the official editor plugin API.
Never access the network.
Never access files except through the editor's API.
Never modify, delete, or create files unless the user has explicitly requested that action through the editor.
Never attempt to bypass or interfere with the editor's security or plugin system.
Never attempt to run any form of ai because it does not comply with the editor's philosophy, that being very similar to UNIX like systems
Plugins that violate these rules are considered unsafe and may be blocked from loading.

bullying or harrassment or vulgar text that is forced into text by the plugin is also restricted.
racist, sexist and discriminatory terms are not permitted as text that can be inserted by a plugin without the user themselves typing the text
